HEADWORD: Purpurin
<hw>Pur"pu*rin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A dyestuff resembling alizarin, found in madder root, and extracted
as an orange or red crystalline substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Purpuriparous</ent>⟦br⟧
